  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I said to him, I said, well-- because I took him on as my interpreter, because I had to have him, because there were so many languages, and there were thousands of Russian in the place.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And then my sergeant major appeared, and I said to him, sergeant major, before this camp was used for this job, it had been a very well maintained regular Kriegsmarine training school.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "I know that because I've seen the sectionized pieces of U-boats, which you would only have in a training school.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And I said, my belief is that the German armed forces didn't work very different to the British, and if that is so, somewhere close to here there will be the garrison engineer who was responsible for all the engineering services in the camp.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And so I said, now, take my jeep, because he rode a motorbike.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You take my jeep and my interpreter, go to the Rathaus, tell them you want the garrison engineer, and it's up to the Rathaus to find him.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Anyway, he when he came back with-- within an hour with this chap.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They found him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And of course, he was put in charge of putting the public utilities back to work.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "That was important because you had to have water, you have to have light, and you had to have various other functions, like sewage functions.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "Because if you didn't, then the lavatories would be blocked, and you'd have a bigger health problem.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Morgan, funnily enough, which is a Welsh name.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Herr Morgan.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And in my memoirs, I pay tribute to him, the work he did, because when the sergeant major brought him in, I spoke to him through my interpreter.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
